        <div class="container">
            <div class="main-content">
                
                <div class="vision-box">
                    <h2>Our Vision</h2>
                    <p>Great government starts with great people doing great work. This policy exists to help every state employee succeed, grow, and contribute to North Carolina's mission of serving its citizens with excellence.</p>
                    <ul style="columns: 2; list-style-type: none; padding: 0;">
                        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> Excellence deserves recognition</li>
                        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> Growth is continuous</li>
                        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> Clarity drives success</li>
                        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> Honest conversations matter</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <section>
                    <h2>What This Means for You</h2>
                    <p>We’ve simplified performance management to focus on people, not paperwork. Select your role to see how this policy supports you:</p>
                    
                    <div class="role-grid">
                        <div class="role-card">
                            <h3><i class="fas fa-user"></i> Employees</h3>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Know exactly what is expected</li>
                                <li>Regular feedback, no surprises</li>
                                <li>Support to grow your career</li>
                                <li>Voice your feedback on supervision</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                        <div class="role-card">
                            <h3><i class="fas fa-user-tie"></i> Supervisors</h3>
                            <ul>
                                <li>More coaching, less paperwork</li>
                                <li>Clear tools and training</li>
                                <li>Authority to recognize excellence</li>
                                <li>Accountable for team success</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                        <div class="role-card">
                            <h3><i class="fas fa-briefcase"></i> HR Professionals</h3>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Flexibility to solve problems</li>
                                <li>Focus on enabling success</li>
                                <li>Better data for better decisions</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </section>

                <section>
                    <h2>How Performance Management Works</h2>
                    <p>Performance management is an ongoing partnership between you and your supervisor built on four simple practices:</p>

                    <div class="step">
                        <div class="step-number">1</div>
                        <div>
                            <strong>Set Clear Goals Together</strong>
                            <p>Agree on 3-5 challenging but achievable goals that connect your work to the agency's mission.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="step">
                        <div class="step-number">2</div>
                        <div>
                            <strong>Talk Regularly About Progress</strong>
                            <p>Quarterly check-ins using a simple framework: <strong>Continue</strong> (what's working), <strong>Start</strong> (new approaches), and <strong>Stop</strong> (what's not working).</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="step">
                        <div class="step-number">3</div>
                        <div>
                            <strong>Get Rated Fairly</strong>
                            <table class="ratings-table">
                                <thead>
                                    <tr>
                                        <th>Rating</th>
                                        <th>Description</th>
                                    </tr>
                                </thead>
                                <tbody>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td><strong>Outstanding</strong></td>
                                        <td>Consistently exceeds expectations</td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td><strong>Successful</strong></td>
                                        <td>Meets expectations and does solid work</td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td><strong>Needs Improvement</strong></td>
                                        <td>Requires support to meet expectations</td>
                                    </tr>
                                </tbody>
                            </table>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="step">
                        <div class="step-number">4</div>
                        <div>
                            <strong>Plan Your Growth</strong>
                            <p>Identify the skills you want to build and the career opportunities you want to pursue.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </section>

                <section>
                    <h2>Core Requirements</h2>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Annual Cycle:</strong> 12-month period including goal setting and quarterly check-ins.</li>
                        <li><strong>Participation:</strong> Includes Permanent, probationary, and time-limited employees.</li>
                        <li><strong>Calibration:</strong> Agencies must review ratings to ensure consistency across teams.</li>
                        <li><strong>Technology:</strong> Progress is tracked via the state's intuitive performance platform.</li>
                    </ul>
                </section>
            </div>

